Name: Crimson Space
Description: Ji'nara's capital ship. Crimson Space can carry the entire Tal'darim combat force on the move, and warp in Death Fleets to tear apart the enemy's defenses. **can be used against ground and air**

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to move to the target area or follow the target unit. Moving units will not engage enemies.
Root.Name: Move

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to cancel all orders and stop moving.
Root.Name: Stop

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to stay where they are and attack enemies that are within range. Units will neither chase down enemies nor move to engage.
Root.Name: Hold Position

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to patrol between their current position and the target area. Units will attack enemies and move to engage nearby enemies.
Root.Name: Patrol

Root.Tooltip: Orders selected units to move to the target point, fighting nearby enemies along the way. Targeting a unit with the Attack command orders that it be attacked until it is destroyed.
Root.Name: Attack

Root.Tooltip:
Crimson Space can load Ji'nara's units and has 24 loading spaces and can load up to 16 unit. Loading different units can provide corresponding buffs to Crimson Space.

When Crimson Space is destroyed, the units loaded inside have a 50% chance of avoiding death.
Root.Name: Ark of Tal'darim

Root.Tooltip: Immediately jumps into target location, deals 80 damage (vs. Armored 100) to enemy units within that area, and stuns them for 8 seconds and deal 10 damage (vs. Armored 20) each seconds.
Root.Name: Gravity Storm

Root.Tooltip:
After a short delay, warps spacetime within the target area. Enemy units and structures within the field will have attack and movement speeds reduced by 115%. During this period, this skill was replaced with "Gravity Storm".

Gravity Storm: Immediately jumps into target location, deals damage to enemy units within that area, and stuns them.
Root.Name: Gravity Bomb

Root.Tooltip: Recalls all allied units in the target area to the user.
Root.Name: Mass Recall

Root.Tooltip:
Warp in Destroyer.

Area assault craft. Can use Destruction Beam to attack multiple units. Can plunder resources when attacking enemy structure.

Can attack ground and air units.
Root.Name: Warp In Destroyer

Root.Tooltip:
Warp in Doom Engine.

Capital ship. Can deal massive area damage and devour Supplicant to gain greater abilities.

Can attack ground and air units.
Root.Name: Warp In Doom Engine

Root.Tooltip: Death Fleets take 20% less damage and gain 50% movement speed when they are near Crimson Space.
Root.Name: Scarlet Curtain

Root.Tooltip: Manage the crews of Crimson Space.
Root.Name: Manage Crews

Root.Tooltip: This unit can detect cloaked, burrowed, and hallucinated units.
Root.Name: Detector

Root.Tooltip: Double Crimson Space's load capacity to 48 supplies, and load limit to 32 units.
Root.Name: Core of Death Star

Root.Tooltip:
Creates a wall of energy at target point, pushing nearby units away and making the terrain impassable. Last 15seconds.

Massive units will remove Force Fields.
Root.Name: Force Field

Root.Tooltip: Each type of unit loaded into Crimson Space will increase 5% bonus damage reduction and 0.5 bonus movement speed for it. Currently loaded 0 types of units.
Root.Name: Beacon of Netherworld

0002.Tooltip: Unload all units other than Tal'darim units in Crimson Space.
0002.Name: Unload Other Units

0002.Tooltip: Drops the current order without performing it, and allows you to select a different order.
0002.Name: Cancel

0002.Tooltip:
Unload Probe.

Each probe in Crimson Space will increase the shield regen by 1, and movement speed by 5.000%.
0002.Name: Unload Probe

0002.Tooltip:
Unload Herald.

Each Herald in Crimson Space will increase the damage to the enemy by 7.50%, sight and detection by 1.00, and weapon range and load range by 0.25, but reduce the movement speed by 5.000%.
0002.Name: Unload Herald

0002.Tooltip:
Unload Supplicant.

Each Supplicant in Crimson Space will increase the health by 200, and health regen by 2, but reduce the movement speed by 5.000%.
0002.Name: Unload Supplicant

0002.Tooltip:
Unload Slaughter.

Each Slaughter in Crimson Space will increase the damage to the enemy by 5%, but reduce the movement speed by 5.000%. Slaughter can attack the enemy inside Crimson Space.
0002.Name: Unload Slaughter

0002.Tooltip:
Unload Blood Hunter.

Each Blood Hunter in Crimson Space will increase the damage to the enemy by 5%, but reduce the movement speed by 5.000%. Blood Hunter can attack the enemy inside Crimson Space.
0002.Name: Unload Blood Hunter

0002.Tooltip:
Unload Ascendent.

Each Ascendent in Crimson Space will increase the damage to the enemy by 7.5%, but reduce the movement speed by 5.0000%. Also, they will increase the damage of Beam of Apocalypse on the top panel.
0002.Name: Unload Ascendant

0002.Tooltip:
Unload Enderwalker.

Each Enderwalker in Crimson Space will increase the damage to the enemy by 10%, and shield armor by 4, but reduce the movement speed by 10.000%. Enderwalker can attack the enemy inside Crimson Space.
0002.Name: Unload Enderwalker

0002.Tooltip:
Unload Martyr.

Each Martyr in Crimson Space will increase the damage to the enemy by 7.5%, but reduce the movement speed by 5.0000%. Also, they will increase the damage of Beam of Apocalypse on the top panel.
0002.Name: Unload Martyr

0002.Tooltip: Unload all units in Crimson Space.
0002.Name: Unload All

Behaviors.Tooltip: Provides power field with corrupted energy.
Behaviors.Name: Blood Pylon Resonance
